# FE navigation (BE-controlled)

Navigation visibility is **owned by the backend**. The FE never hardcodes admin menu items in layout components.

## How it works

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Auth as AuthService
    participant Nav as NavigationService
    participant API as GET_api_navigation_my
    participant Layout as MainLayout

    Auth->>API: loadMe then navigation.load
    API-->>Nav: NavigationItemDto[] filtered by permissions
    Nav-->>Layout: menuItems$ PrimeNG MenuItem[]
```

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| BE `NavigationCatalog` | Static list: path, icon, label key, `RequiredPermission` |
| BE `GetMyNavigationHandler` | Filter items by user permissions (`IPermissionCache`) |
| BE `GET /api/navigation/my` | Returns only allowed items for current user |
| FE `NavigationService` | Calls `NavigationClient.my()`, exposes `menuItems$` |
| FE `permissionGuard` | Blocks direct URL access when permission missing |

## FE rules (do / don't)

**Do:**
- Use [`NavigationService`](src/iM.Cloud.Client/src/app/core/navigation/navigation.service.ts) for menubar: `menuItems$` in [`MainLayoutComponent`](src/iM.Cloud.Client/src/app/layout/main-layout/main-layout.component.ts).
- Load navigation after auth session is established — [`AuthService.loadMe()`](src/iM.Cloud.Client/src/app/core/auth/auth.service.ts) chains `navigation.load()`; `clearSession()` calls `navigation.clear()`.
- Protect restricted routes with [`permissionGuard`](src/iM.Cloud.Client/src/app/core/auth/permission.guard.ts) + `data: { permission: '...' }` in [`app.routes.ts`](src/iM.Cloud.Client/src/app/app.routes.ts). Permission must match BE `PermissionCodes` / `RequirePermission` on the API.
- Treat `NavigationItemDto.label` as an **i18n translation key** (e.g. `nav.users`), not display text. Wire `TranslateService` when i18n is added.
- Use generated [`NavigationClient`](clients/angular/im-cloud-api-client.ts) from `@im-cloud/api` — regenerate via `./scripts/generate-api-client.sh` after BE DTO changes.

**Don't:**
- Hardcode `MenuItem[]` in layout or feature components for app-wide navigation.
- Rely on hiding menu entries alone — users can type URLs; always use `permissionGuard` on protected routes.
- Edit `clients/angular/im-cloud-api-client.ts` by hand.

## Adding a new navigable page

1. **BE** — add entry to [`NavigationCatalog.cs`](src/iM.Cloud.Application/Navigation/NavigationCatalog.cs): `Key`, `Label` (`nav.*`), `Icon`, `Path`, `Order`, `RequiredPermission` (or `null` for public).
2. **FE route** — add lazy route in `app.routes.ts` with `canActivate: [permissionGuard]` and `data.permission` matching the catalog permission.
3. **FE i18n** — add `nav.*` label key (when translation files exist).
4. Regenerate API client if `NavigationItemDto` shape changes.

## Permission alignment

| Catalog permission | Example path | API guard |
|--------------------|--------------|-----------|
| `users.read` | `/admin/users` | `RequirePermission(UsersRead)` |
| `roles.manage` | `/admin/roles` | `RequirePermission(RolesManage)` |
| `groups.read` | `/admin/groups` | `RequirePermission(GroupsRead)` |

Admin role has all permissions → sees all catalog items. Limited users see and access only matching items.

## Checklist (agent)

- New admin screen → BE catalog row + FE route + `permissionGuard` + same permission string as BE.
- Layout/menu work → use `NavigationService`, not local `menuItems` arrays.
- After login/navigation API change → verify menubar and direct URL both respect permissions.
